        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": " feat: add Spectrum by Photon iMessage channel plugin for OpenClaw ",
        "body": "AI-assisted: I used Codex to help implement, test, and prepare this PR.\nI reviewed the changes and understand what the code does.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nResolves a problem where iMessage support currently depends on the\nmacOS-only `imsg` CLI channel. Users who want to run OpenClaw on Linux,\nWindows, WSL, containers, or servers cannot use iMessage without a Mac-\nbacked setup.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a separate iMessage Spectrum channel powered by Photon\nSpectrum, keeping it independent from the existing macOS `imsg` CLI\nchannel. The plugin includes Spectrum runtime wiring, inbound and\noutbound message routing, iMessage effects, explicit reply handling,\nwebhook onboarding, health diagnostics, and focused regression tests.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can configure an iMessage channel without requiring macOS or the\n`imsg` CLI. The onboarding flow guides users through Photon project\ncredentials, webhook URL setup, and generating the webhook signing\nsecret with a curl command.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Ran `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage-spectrum`\n- Result: passed\n- Coverage: 3 test files, 18 tests\n- Validates:\n  - Spectrum account setup and config patching\n  - Photon webhook curl generation during onboarding\n  - iMessage effect alias parsing\n  - explicit reply/thread handling\n  - catchup cursor seeding so old messages are not replayed as new inbound turns\n  - runtime wiring regression coverage for the iMessage Spectrum channel\n- Added `docs/channels/imessage-spectrum.md`, config schema, labeler wiring, bundled channel metadata, and `pnpm-lock.yaml` updates for `spectrum-ts`\n\nTypecheck note:\n- Focused extension tests report no `imessage-spectrum` TypeScript errors",
